Utilization of Canadian manufacturingcapacity rose to 77.2 pct in the fourth quarter of 1986 from 77pct in the third quarter, Statistics Canada said.    "Although the change was small, this marked the firstquarter since the third quarter of 1985 in which theutilization rates for manufacturing as a whole rose," thefederal agency said.    Increased residential construction led to strong increasesin the building materials sector, led by a 3.3 pct increase innon-metallic mineral industries. Reuter&#3;